Martha was with her owner on the beach in Leasowe in Merseyside when she was swept out to sea by the tide . 
  The golden retriever was caught in a strong current and her owner tried to rescue her from the water . 
  But New Brighton RNLI crew were called to rescue the dog who was cold and shivering . 
  Martha was pulled on to the lifeboat after being found half a mile away . 
  RNLI have warned owners not to attempt to rescue their pets at sea . 
 